    "publication": [
        {
            "abstract": "Â© 2015 The Author. All rights reserved. Diffusion maps are a spectral method for non-linear dimension reduction and have recently been adapted for the visualization of single-cell expression data. Here we present destiny, an efficient R implementation of the diffusion map algorithm. Our package includes a single-cell specific noise model allowing for missing and censored values. In contrast to previous implementations, we further present an efficient nearest-neighbour approximation that allows for the processing of hundreds of thousands of cells and a functionality for projecting new data on existing diffusion maps. We exemplarily apply destiny to a recent time-resolved mass cytometry dataset of cellular reprogramming.",
            "authors": [
                "Angerer P.",
                "Haghverdi L.",
                "Buttner M.",
                "Theis F.J.",
                "Marr C.",
                "Buettner F."
            ],
            "cit_count": 65,
            "doi": "10.1093/bioinformatics/btv715",
            "journal": "Bioinformatics",
            "title": "Destiny: Diffusion maps for large-scale single-cell data in R",
            "type": "Primary",
